10/04/2003
BAGHDAD, Iraq -- Veteran Bulgarian war correspondent Elena Yoncheva reports she was attacked by armed robbers in Baghdad.
She says she and six Portuguese journalists were beaten and robbed, then saved only after intervention by two Iraqis, one of whom spoke Bulgarian.
Yoncheva, of the national BNT, is the only Bulgarian correspondent in Iraq.
She has covered fighting in Afghanistan, Yugoslavia and Chechnya.
(Dnevnik, Trud, Monitor, 24 Chassa - 10/04/03;
BNT, BNR, BTA - 09/04/03)
